# This file contains some sample properties
# for setting of logging of a Cougaar system,
# using the Cougaar logging service.

# The Cougaar logging service simply uses Log4J, so 
# for complete instructions, see the Log4J documentation
# http://jakarta.apache.org/log4j/docs/manual.html

# For details on the Cougaar logging service, see
#  doc/details/Logging.html

# To specify a custom set of logging properties, supply to your Node
# the property -Dorg.cougaar.core.logging.config.filename=<File on
# Config Path>

# Here is the default, which is used if you specify no separate
# logging file
log4j.rootCategory=WARN,A1
log4j.appender.A1=org.apache.log4j.ConsoleAppender
log4j.appender.A1.layout=org.apache.log4j.PatternLayout
log4j.appender.A1.layout.ConversionPattern==%d{ABSOLUTE} %-5p - %c{1} - %m%n

# You can then add lines below this to log other components at a
# different level
# set the level to "info" for all "org.cougaar.core.*" subpackages:
#log4j.category.org.cougaar.core=INFO

# debug your "com.foo.MyPlugin":
#log4j.category.com.foo.MyPlugin=DEBUG


# Alternatively, many Cougaar developers may wish to send logging to a logging
# server, like Lumbermill (http://traxel.com/lumbermill). Here is
# what your logging properties file should use to send logging to lumbermill
#log4j.rootCategory=DEBUG,LogServer
#log4j.appender.LogServer=org.apache.log4j.net.SocketAppender
#log4j.appender.LogServer.Port=4445
#log4j.appender.LogServer.RemoteHost=127.0.0.1
